{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C2vpSr9uaKt7A7MVnvbuhh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’---\n     2â†’name: deterministic-service-test\n     3â†’description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4â†’---\n     5â†’\n     6â†’# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7â†’\n     8â†’Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9â†’Implement the file edits directly. Do not return a checklist-only response.\n    10â†’\n    11â†’## Required Variables\n    12â†’\n    13â†’- `service_symbol`\n    14â†’- `module_path`\n    15â†’- `create_method`\n    16â†’- `cancel_method`\n    17â†’\n    18â†’## Required Output Contract\n    19â†’\n    20â†’1. Write `tests/test_core_service.py`.\n    21â†’2. Import `datetime` from `datetime`, `create_autospec` from `unittest.mock`, `pytest`, and `CoreService` from `services.core_service`.\n    22â†’3. Define a `fixed_check_in` fixture that returns `datetime(2024, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0)`.\n    23â†’4. Define `test_create_record_returns_confirmed_status(fixed_check_in)`.\n    24â†’5. In that test:\n    25â†’- instantiate `service = CoreService()`\n    26â†’- instantiate `notifier = create_autospec(object, spec_set=True)`\n    27â†’- include a visible `# Act` comment immediately before the service call\n    28â†’- call `service.create_record(display_name=\"Alice\", check_in=fixed_check_in, check_out=datetime(2024, 1, 3, 12, 0, 0))`\n    29â†’- assert `result[\"status\"] == \"confirmed\"`\n    30â†’- assert `notifier.mock_calls == []`\n    31â†’6. Define `test_cancel_record_returns_cancelled_status()`.\n    32â†’7. In that test:\n    33â†’- instantiate `service = CoreService()`\n    34â†’- include a visible `# Act` comment immediately before the service call\n    35â†’- call `service.cancel_record(record_id=\"abc-123\")`\n    36â†’- assert `result[\"status\"] == \"cancelled\"`\n    37â†’8. Preserve the exact test names above and keep one behavior per test.\n    38â†’\n    39â†’## Guardrails\n    40â†’\n    41â†’- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    42â†’- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    43â†’- Do not add extra helper abstractions or additional tests beyond the required contract.\n    44â†’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37e047b1-923d-4d5e-8c03-738051b8e60f","uuid":"790d77e5-7e8a-4bb2-a958-efe445653651"}
